WEBVTT

00:06.484 --> 00:06.702
.

00:06.745 --> 00:08.443
- Previously on "Colony"...

00:09.313 --> 00:10.140
- Total rendition is coming.

00:11.228 --> 00:12.403
Our glorious Hosts round up every human

00:12.447 --> 00:14.318
they can find and take them to the factory.

00:14.362 --> 00:16.059
- We have to go.

00:16.103 --> 00:17.713
Another war's starting,
and it's not safe here.

00:17.756 --> 00:19.280
I didn't know where else
to take her.

00:19.323 --> 00:20.716
- I want to know
where Kynes went.

00:20.759 --> 00:22.544
- There are two officers
in my division

00:22.587 --> 00:23.719
that you should talk to.

00:23.762 --> 00:25.590
- Go.
I'll keep them busy.

00:27.114 --> 00:28.245
- There she is.

00:28.289 --> 00:30.465
- Kynes is hit.

00:30.508 --> 00:32.249
- All clear. Moving out.

00:35.296 --> 00:38.342
♪

00:38.386 --> 00:42.042
[indistinct chatter,
telephones ringing]

00:54.880 --> 00:57.796
- The rumors are true.
The attack has begun.

00:59.146 --> 01:01.104
As expected, the enemy fleet

01:01.148 --> 01:03.498
has breached
our incomplete space wall.

01:03.541 --> 01:05.674
The fight will happen
in the skies above us.

01:05.717 --> 01:09.112
But we should anticipate that
some of our facilities on Earth

01:09.156 --> 01:11.158
will be bombarded as well.

01:13.160 --> 01:16.206
- I have been assured that the
shield above Davos will hold.

01:16.250 --> 01:19.209
And there is a secondary shield
above this bunker.

01:19.253 --> 01:20.732
- Can we bring our families
to the facility?

01:20.776 --> 01:22.343
- I would recommend that, yes.

01:22.386 --> 01:25.215
- Well, what's gonna happen
to the Colonies?

01:25.259 --> 01:29.350
- I expect that we will lose
a few of them.

01:33.658 --> 01:35.530
We knew that this
day was coming,

01:35.573 --> 01:37.445
and we are prepared.

01:38.924 --> 01:42.711
When our Hosts win this war--
and they will win--

01:42.754 --> 01:44.887
our sacrifices will be repaid.

01:47.411 --> 01:50.153
It will be...

01:50.197 --> 01:52.503
humanity's greatest day.

01:54.723 --> 01:58.205
- I got Tinkerbell, ma'am.
- Oh.

01:58.248 --> 02:00.294
Don't look so glum.

02:00.337 --> 02:01.904
We only have to be here
for a little while.

02:06.648 --> 02:08.432
- Good news, I'm sure.

02:08.476 --> 02:11.435
[blaring continues,
indistinct nervous chatter]

02:21.315 --> 02:22.446
- Seal the doors!

02:30.498 --> 02:32.630
- Everybody go!

02:35.807 --> 02:42.858
♪

03:04.619 --> 03:10.277
♪

03:14.716 --> 03:19.416
♪

03:39.741 --> 03:46.748
♪

03:53.581 --> 03:56.279
- Stop!

03:57.759 --> 04:00.544
♪

04:05.114 --> 04:09.988
♪

04:12.774 --> 04:15.733
- Excuse me,
I'm looking for Sean Dalton.

04:15.777 --> 04:17.561
He's with the patrol.

04:17.605 --> 04:19.694
- We're on lockdown.

04:19.737 --> 04:22.827
- I have information about
a dangerous group of refugees.

04:33.621 --> 04:35.013
- You disappeared,
and I was worried.

04:35.057 --> 04:37.625
- I got called in.

04:37.668 --> 04:41.324
- Safe.

04:41.368 --> 04:43.674
- She's staying with
some friends of mine.

04:43.718 --> 04:47.417
- Okay.
I need to see her.

04:47.461 --> 04:49.027
- Not now.

04:51.682 --> 04:54.859
- That's not your decision.
I'm her mother.

04:54.903 --> 04:58.602
- I'm sorry.
This is the way it has to be.

04:58.646 --> 05:00.735
We finally found
something good in Seattle.

05:00.778 --> 05:02.389
We've been safe here.

05:02.432 --> 05:05.740
Now you and Dad are trying
to mess that up.

05:05.783 --> 05:08.830
I don't care.
Do whatever you want.

05:10.484 --> 05:12.355
But when they catch you,

05:12.399 --> 05:14.618
they aren't gonna take Gracie
because she'll be with me.

05:14.662 --> 05:15.837
- Bram...

05:15.880 --> 05:18.666
- We can't talk
about this here.

05:18.709 --> 05:21.103
You need to leave.

05:21.146 --> 05:22.931
- Bram.

05:22.974 --> 05:24.759
- All I have to do
is snap my fingers,

05:24.802 --> 05:27.457
and they'll take you away.

05:27.501 --> 05:29.459
Is that what you want?

05:30.547 --> 05:32.984
- Your father and I
never wanted for you

05:33.028 --> 05:34.682
to be involved in this.

05:37.772 --> 05:40.122
- Then why'd Dad ask me
to help him kill Snyder?

05:43.473 --> 05:45.997
You've made your choice.

05:46.041 --> 05:47.564
Just go.

05:50.611 --> 05:57.661
♪

06:02.884 --> 06:05.713
- They tell me you've been
in here sulking all morning.

06:07.976 --> 06:09.717
I got some good news.

06:10.892 --> 06:14.722
We captured one of the outliers
that abducted Kynes.

06:14.765 --> 06:17.551
He's an old friend of yours...

06:17.594 --> 06:19.117
Will Bowman.

06:24.558 --> 06:27.169
You know, I am not a man
that scares easily,

06:27.212 --> 06:31.042
but something very, very bad
must have happened

06:31.086 --> 06:33.393
if your mouth isn't running.

06:36.091 --> 06:38.180
- The attack has begun.

06:41.575 --> 06:43.054
- Yeah.

06:44.229 --> 06:46.536
What are our orders?

06:46.580 --> 06:49.409
- We have no orders.

06:55.502 --> 06:57.242
Apparently...

06:57.286 --> 07:00.724
some sort of commando force
hit Davos.

07:00.768 --> 07:03.901
IGA leadership is either
dead or captured.

07:08.689 --> 07:10.560
- For emergency use--

07:10.604 --> 07:13.171
a direct line to our Hosts.

07:13.215 --> 07:16.697
I'm supposed to call it
to receive my instructions.

07:18.742 --> 07:22.093
- Well, what the hell
are you waiting for?

07:22.137 --> 07:24.922
- What if we've picked
the wrong side?

07:27.795 --> 07:31.146
- It is a little late for that.

07:38.066 --> 07:39.850
- Okay, then...

07:41.112 --> 07:43.941
Let's play the hand
that we were dealt.

07:43.985 --> 07:47.728
I should begin with some
questions for Mr. Bowman.

07:47.771 --> 07:49.294
Can he still talk,

07:49.338 --> 07:51.253
or have you carved his tongue
out of his mouth?

07:51.296 --> 07:53.777
- Oh, he can talk.
I'm not sure he wants to.

07:53.821 --> 07:55.300
- Oh, Will and I go back.

07:55.344 --> 07:57.868
I'm sure he'll open up
like an oyster.

07:59.174 --> 08:01.524
Give me a minute.

08:13.014 --> 08:15.799
Hello, Will.

08:15.843 --> 08:17.758
How come every time
we talk these days,

08:17.801 --> 08:19.629
one of us is tied to a chair?

08:19.673 --> 08:22.893
- Who would talk to you if they
weren't tied to a chair?

08:22.937 --> 08:24.329
- Many people, actually.

08:24.373 --> 08:27.637
It seems my star
is once again on the rise.

08:27.681 --> 08:29.813
Might take time,

08:29.857 --> 08:32.250
but eventually they'll see you
for what you are.

08:36.603 --> 08:39.214
You've lost your center,
haven't you?

08:39.257 --> 08:41.869
I saw it in that
shitty little room

08:41.912 --> 08:44.567
where you tried to drown me.

08:44.611 --> 08:47.527
And I don't think it's just
about what happened to Charlie.

08:49.572 --> 08:52.183
We all have stains
on our conscience.

08:53.750 --> 08:55.839
I keep thinking about the
people I sent to the factory

08:55.883 --> 08:57.667
back in Los Angeles.

08:57.711 --> 09:00.278
It's my fault they're all dead.

09:02.759 --> 09:05.283
- What do you mean
they're all dead?

09:06.937 --> 09:09.853
- The factory was destroyed
in a sneak attack

09:09.897 --> 09:13.161
by our Hosts' enemies--
no survivors.

09:15.903 --> 09:19.297
The human race
is in a fight for survival.

09:20.995 --> 09:23.388
And I need your help.

09:23.432 --> 09:25.608
- That's why you're
patching me up.

09:25.652 --> 09:27.697
- I've just heard
from our Hosts.

09:27.741 --> 09:30.004
If they don't choose
to defend this Colony,

09:30.047 --> 09:31.919
we will be annihilated
from space.

09:31.962 --> 09:33.921
Nothing will be left
but a smoking crater.

09:35.705 --> 09:38.142
- Because we haven't been
meeting our outlier quota.

09:38.186 --> 09:40.710
It's like a military draft.

09:40.754 --> 09:43.060
A certain number
of people like you

09:43.104 --> 09:45.062
are supposed
to be getting into pods,

09:45.106 --> 09:48.152
but Everett Kynes
has been skimming off the top.

09:50.067 --> 09:52.722
So that's what
our Hosts told me.

09:52.766 --> 09:56.030
Either 150 outliers
show up at the island

09:56.073 --> 09:58.902
by the end of the day...

09:58.946 --> 10:01.775
or they'll turn
their backs on us.

10:08.129 --> 10:11.001
When I walked into your kitchen
in Los Angeles,

10:11.045 --> 10:12.786
I didn't pick you
to work for me

10:12.829 --> 10:15.397
because you were
a good detective.

10:15.440 --> 10:19.183
I picked you because
you were a good man.

10:20.315 --> 10:21.925
- You took advantage of me,

10:21.969 --> 10:23.753
and you're trying
to do it again.

10:23.797 --> 10:26.756
- You're right to be skeptical.
After all, I am a known liar.

10:26.800 --> 10:28.932
But put yourself in my shoes.

10:28.976 --> 10:32.022
Do you really think I'd be
sitting in here with you

10:32.066 --> 10:33.937
if I didn't have to?

10:35.809 --> 10:38.942
I don't have the time
or the resources

10:38.986 --> 10:41.771
to round up those outliers
by the end of the day.

10:41.815 --> 10:46.471
So I'm counting on you
to go and tell them--

10:46.515 --> 10:49.823
either they sacrifice
themselves...

10:49.866 --> 10:52.086
or we all die.

10:55.437 --> 10:57.657
- You're letting me
out of here?

11:01.182 --> 11:02.966
- Maybe I was wrong.

11:04.185 --> 11:07.101
Maybe you are too far gone.

11:07.144 --> 11:11.714
But this is your chance to save
Katie and Gracie and Bram.

11:14.761 --> 11:21.724
♪

11:21.768 --> 11:24.292
Good-bye, Will Bowman.

11:24.335 --> 11:28.252
I hope I never see you
or your family again.

11:39.524 --> 11:39.916
.

11:53.277 --> 11:54.801
- Alive.

11:58.282 --> 12:01.590
- Doing my best.
- Oh...

12:01.633 --> 12:02.939
Sorry.

12:08.510 --> 12:11.165
- Got a lot of soldiers--
good ones, I think--

12:11.208 --> 12:13.428
But no real leader.

12:13.471 --> 12:16.126
- Did you ever consider
nominating yourself?

12:16.170 --> 12:17.780
- That's not what I do.

12:17.824 --> 12:19.521
Give me a mission,
I'll execute it.

12:19.564 --> 12:21.262
But I'm not one for speeches.

12:21.305 --> 12:23.177
- They don't need a speech.
They need a direction.

12:23.220 --> 12:25.048
- Don't have that either.

12:26.267 --> 12:27.834
- Sure you do.

12:29.444 --> 12:32.577
I know it's easier to just
be the man with the gun,

12:32.621 --> 12:35.319
keep pulling the trigger,
hoping for orders...

12:36.581 --> 12:38.366
But that magical person
you're waiting for--

12:38.409 --> 12:40.281
they're not coming.

12:40.324 --> 12:41.325
It's just us.

12:42.631 --> 12:44.851
Those people out there
will listen to you.

12:54.904 --> 13:01.955
♪

13:33.290 --> 13:37.947
- Will you pledge allegiance
to the Interim Global Authority

13:37.991 --> 13:41.864
and the Colony of Seattle
and swear to give your life

13:41.908 --> 13:45.172
to defend them
from all enemies?

13:45.215 --> 13:47.174
And will you further pledge

13:47.217 --> 13:49.350
to give
your unconditional obedience

13:49.393 --> 13:52.266
to Proxy Alan Snyder?

13:52.309 --> 13:54.355
all: I will.

14:04.104 --> 14:07.368
- You know how
to work that thing?

14:07.411 --> 14:08.935
- Kind of.

14:08.978 --> 14:10.588
- You know, I was the one
who recommended you

14:10.632 --> 14:12.112
for this new unit.

14:12.155 --> 14:13.635
I think you're gonna do great.

14:13.678 --> 14:15.202
- Thanks.

14:20.990 --> 14:23.427
- I didn't know your mom
was an advocate.

14:26.169 --> 14:28.302
- I looked her up
in the system.

14:28.345 --> 14:30.695
You and Gracie
are staying in my home.

14:30.739 --> 14:33.220
Had to make sure we're all
on the right side.

14:36.092 --> 14:39.574
- It's gonna get tough
in the Colony.

14:39.617 --> 14:42.142
But if we keep our mouths shut,
follow orders,

14:42.185 --> 14:43.491
we'll get through.

14:46.450 --> 14:47.930
You understand?

14:51.020 --> 14:52.108
- Yeah.

15:03.990 --> 15:06.383
- So there it is.

15:06.427 --> 15:09.256
We just got to decide
if we believe it.

15:09.299 --> 15:11.171
- I don't know.

15:11.214 --> 15:14.304
Feels like a good way to get
150 of our guys off the street.

15:14.348 --> 15:16.785
- Maybe.

15:16.828 --> 15:19.744
- I've given up trying
to read that man.

15:19.788 --> 15:21.703
But if he isn't lying...

15:21.746 --> 15:24.097
- We should try to confirm at
least some of what he's saying.

15:24.140 --> 15:25.620
Maybe we can find
a telescope

15:25.663 --> 15:27.100
and take a look
at that factory.

15:27.143 --> 15:28.536
Just 'cause

15:28.579 --> 15:30.277
he's telling the truth
about the factory

15:30.320 --> 15:31.974
doesn't mean he isn't lying
about everything else.

15:32.018 --> 15:33.715
- What if we got up on
the IGA communications network?

15:33.758 --> 15:35.325
If this attack
has already begun,

15:35.369 --> 15:37.240
there must be all
kinds of chatter.

15:37.284 --> 15:39.634
- I saw a secure radio facility
back at that place we hit.

15:39.677 --> 15:41.636
- No, we can't go
back there.

15:41.679 --> 15:43.464
- It also had heavy armory.

15:43.507 --> 15:45.205
If we're gonna keep engaging
with those Grayhats,

15:45.248 --> 15:46.815
we need better weapons.

15:46.858 --> 15:48.469
- It won't matter what kind
of weapons are inside

15:48.512 --> 15:49.731
if we get wiped out.

15:49.774 --> 15:51.211
It's got to be
another facility.

15:51.254 --> 15:52.603
- I'm sure there is,
but the guy who knows

15:52.647 --> 15:55.476
the location is bleeding
out in the other room.

15:55.519 --> 15:57.478
How long do we have?

15:57.521 --> 15:59.088
- Not long.

16:02.309 --> 16:04.485
- We're gonna hit
that place again.

16:04.528 --> 16:06.487
It's our best option.

16:06.530 --> 16:09.011
- Mine.

16:11.100 --> 16:12.493
- I don't know you.

16:12.536 --> 16:14.495
- The Occupation will never
expect us to hit

16:14.538 --> 16:16.410
that facility again.

16:16.453 --> 16:18.151
They don't have
unlimited manpower,

16:18.194 --> 16:21.632
so my guess is it's guarded
by a skeleton crew.

16:21.676 --> 16:23.634
We'll leverage our intel
from the previous attack,

16:23.678 --> 16:25.680
go in hard and fast,
and take the information

16:25.723 --> 16:27.508
and weapons we need
to fight this war.

16:27.551 --> 16:34.515
♪

16:34.558 --> 16:37.126
- I'll tell everybody
to strap up.

16:49.443 --> 16:49.704
.

16:49.747 --> 16:51.793
- You were right.

16:53.273 --> 16:54.013
Looks like it's being guarded
by a skeleton crew.

16:54.622 --> 16:55.579
- At least on the outside.

16:57.016 --> 16:57.059
- We've had eyes on the
entrance of the motor pool

16:58.191 --> 16:58.365
for over an hour--
nothing in or out.

16:59.409 --> 17:00.323
- Got to think
they'll respond fast.

17:02.282 --> 17:05.067
Nearest big facility is here.

17:05.111 --> 17:07.156
Even if they mobilize
instantly and haul ass,

17:07.200 --> 17:08.244
it's 15 minutes.

17:08.288 --> 17:11.508
- The local units will rally.

17:11.552 --> 17:14.120
- Ten of us will go inside.

17:14.163 --> 17:16.600
Everyone else finds cover and
ambushes the first responders

17:16.644 --> 17:18.167
when they arrive.

17:18.211 --> 17:20.778
Once my team is clear,
we all melt away--

17:20.822 --> 17:23.607
guerrilla style.

17:28.134 --> 17:35.184
♪

17:50.504 --> 17:52.897
- I'm looking for my husband.

17:52.941 --> 17:55.683
- He's out...
with Broussard.

17:57.641 --> 17:59.382
How did you find us?

17:59.426 --> 18:01.645
- I went to the gym,
and they said you were here.

18:04.257 --> 18:06.302
Are you okay?

18:07.825 --> 18:09.088
- No.

18:14.615 --> 18:18.662
My boyfriend was an oncologist
in Seattle before the Arrival.

18:21.578 --> 18:23.537
I knew the whole city
was renditioned,

18:23.580 --> 18:28.498
but when I got here, I couldn't
help looking for him.

18:31.197 --> 18:34.591
I had this stupid fantasy
that he'd hidden

18:34.635 --> 18:37.290
in a basement somewhere.

18:37.333 --> 18:40.293
- And he's at the factory.

18:42.251 --> 18:43.383
- Probably.

18:47.561 --> 18:50.477
And now that's gone,
and all those people are dead.

18:54.220 --> 18:56.396
♪

18:56.439 --> 18:59.834
- I'm sorry. You must've
had friends there, too.

19:01.662 --> 19:08.712
♪

19:12.325 --> 19:13.978
- I don't know you.

19:14.022 --> 19:16.285
♪

19:16.329 --> 19:18.505
But I know you must
be incredibly strong

19:18.548 --> 19:19.854
to have made it this far.

19:22.291 --> 19:25.381
Well, I used to believe
in something. That helped.

19:29.603 --> 19:32.475
- I don't know if the things
I believe all fit together.

19:32.519 --> 19:34.477
♪

19:34.521 --> 19:37.828
- Nothing fits
together anymore.

19:37.872 --> 19:40.831
That's just the way it is.

19:40.875 --> 19:43.312
You can't blame
yourself for that.

19:43.356 --> 19:46.750
♪

19:46.794 --> 19:50.841
At some point,
things have to turn around.

19:50.885 --> 19:52.016
They have to get better.

19:52.060 --> 19:54.497
I don't know.

19:54.541 --> 19:56.543
♪

19:56.586 --> 19:58.849
What are we doing
to make it better?

19:58.893 --> 20:03.941
♪

20:03.985 --> 20:07.467
- Everyone, grab your guns.
Meet me outside.

20:07.510 --> 20:09.251
Now.

20:09.295 --> 20:11.775
- Some kind of attack.

20:11.819 --> 20:13.037
Move!

20:15.736 --> 20:19.348
- This is taking too long.
- We've got no grenades.

20:19.392 --> 20:21.611
- Cover me.

20:21.655 --> 20:28.488
♪

20:32.535 --> 20:35.277
- That was bullshit.
- Let's go.

20:35.321 --> 20:37.323
♪

20:37.366 --> 20:38.802
- Get started on the armory.

20:38.846 --> 20:40.891
We need to be out of here
in three minutes.

20:40.935 --> 20:42.893
♪

20:42.937 --> 20:44.982
- It's down this street.

20:45.026 --> 20:47.594
- More guys coming behind.
I'm gonna stay and coordinate.

20:47.637 --> 20:49.378
- Fine.
The rest of you follow me.

20:52.425 --> 20:59.475
♪

21:15.404 --> 21:16.449
- Nate!

21:23.934 --> 21:30.985
♪

21:41.474 --> 21:43.780
♪

21:43.824 --> 21:46.870
[man speaking Spanish
over radio]

21:53.486 --> 21:55.314
- Barely enough to order
a cerveza.

21:56.793 --> 21:59.448
- Lo siento,
no hablo español.

21:59.492 --> 22:01.972
- Yes.

22:02.016 --> 22:03.800
This is Seattle.
Who are you?

22:03.844 --> 22:06.934
- This is Buenos Aires,
Region Five.

22:06.977 --> 22:08.805
- Sí.

22:08.849 --> 22:11.808
It started this morning.

22:11.852 --> 22:13.810
- The ones they warned
us would come--

22:13.854 --> 22:15.551
los demonios.

22:23.298 --> 22:23.429
.

22:30.697 --> 22:32.786
- You asked for him
to help you.

22:34.004 --> 22:36.355
- Killing Snyder.

22:38.008 --> 22:39.880
- He wanted to be a part of it.

22:39.923 --> 22:41.403
He's a child.

22:41.447 --> 22:44.754
- He's 19.
- And our son.

22:44.798 --> 22:46.190
What's wrong with you?

22:47.453 --> 22:49.324
- Don't lecture me.

22:49.368 --> 22:51.935
You put our whole family
at risk in LA.

22:51.979 --> 22:53.807
- You knew that involving
Bram was wrong.

22:53.850 --> 22:56.113
That's why you lied
about it to my face.

22:56.157 --> 22:58.159
- Like you lied to me
100 different times.

22:58.202 --> 23:00.814
- I never lied about putting
our children in danger.

23:00.857 --> 23:03.382
- You put everyone in danger.

23:03.425 --> 23:05.775
You and Broussard got the whole
damn block renditioned,

23:05.819 --> 23:07.168
remember?

23:08.909 --> 23:10.911
- I can't do this.

23:12.042 --> 23:16.133
We've lost everyone.

23:16.177 --> 23:19.485
We have no family.
We have no old friends.

23:19.528 --> 23:21.269
We need each other.

23:23.793 --> 23:26.709
And it's like you're just gone.

23:34.761 --> 23:38.417
I thought I knew how hard
it was gonna be...

23:38.460 --> 23:41.202
when we lost Charlie.

23:41.245 --> 23:43.857
I never expected
to go through it alone.

23:43.900 --> 23:45.859
- That's not fair.

23:47.904 --> 23:50.429
- I did good work
in that refugee camp.

23:52.256 --> 23:54.781
I tried to make a difference
and be a good mom

23:54.824 --> 23:56.435
and hold it all together.

23:58.785 --> 24:01.309
And you never saw
'cause you weren't looking.

24:04.007 --> 24:06.401
- I told you last night
you're better off without me.

24:06.445 --> 24:10.013
- Don't.
Don't quit on us.

24:16.455 --> 24:19.806
- I don't know how to dig
myself out of this hole.

24:25.159 --> 24:27.901
- Start by being honest...

24:27.944 --> 24:30.904
with me, with yourself.

24:30.947 --> 24:33.776
You don't have to pretend
you're okay when you're not.

24:48.965 --> 24:50.271
- No.

24:52.360 --> 24:54.362
- It's Bram's girlfriend.

24:55.972 --> 25:00.455
He took Gracie, and he went
to go stay with her.

25:00.499 --> 25:03.197
Our son has
a whole secret life.

25:07.244 --> 25:09.116
- We failed them.

25:10.596 --> 25:15.209
- Yeah.
But we can fix it.

25:17.951 --> 25:20.344
- We don't worry
about the big stuff

25:20.388 --> 25:23.478
until we fix the small stuff.

25:23.522 --> 25:25.306
We put them first.

25:29.658 --> 25:31.486
- We got to find them.

25:31.530 --> 25:34.489
- It's a big Colony.

25:34.533 --> 25:37.448
- I can do an image search
out at the refugee camp,

25:37.492 --> 25:39.189
get an address.

25:47.197 --> 25:49.504
- Let me see what
I can find out here.

25:49.548 --> 25:51.985
Figure out if it's--

25:52.028 --> 25:53.987
if we're better off
staying in Seattle

25:54.030 --> 25:56.555
or getting outside the Walls.

26:02.648 --> 26:04.040
Hey.

26:07.130 --> 26:09.132
I'm proud of you.

26:09.176 --> 26:12.266
You always fight
for what matters.

26:13.659 --> 26:16.313
The kids will see that one day.

26:18.707 --> 26:23.016
Find the kids,
bunker down somewhere safe.

26:23.059 --> 26:26.628
When I've got a plan,
I'll find you.

26:26.672 --> 26:33.896
♪

26:50.696 --> 26:54.395
- Welcome back.

26:54.438 --> 26:56.136
Where am I?

26:57.441 --> 26:59.618
- With friends.
- Mm.

27:02.446 --> 27:04.318
Is it bad?

27:06.146 --> 27:07.713
- Yeah.

27:10.629 --> 27:13.109
- I don't know.

27:14.110 --> 27:15.503
Without an MRI machine,

27:15.546 --> 27:19.028
I can't tell if you're still
bleeding internally.

27:19.072 --> 27:22.249
- Amy.

27:24.730 --> 27:26.993
- Very.

27:29.212 --> 27:31.650
But this isn't exactly
my specialty.

27:33.477 --> 27:35.001
- There's a full
medical facility

27:35.044 --> 27:36.480
at my bunker in Bellevue--

27:36.524 --> 27:39.614
food, supplies, water...

27:39.658 --> 27:42.095
whatever else you
and your friends need.

27:42.138 --> 27:44.967
- I have some questions first.

27:45.011 --> 27:46.665
- Not now.

27:46.708 --> 27:49.145
- It's all right.

27:49.189 --> 27:53.541
I can't expect them to fight
if they don't know why.

27:57.458 --> 27:59.590
- Yo.

27:59.634 --> 28:01.680
Eyes front.

28:03.769 --> 28:06.206
I've got news.

28:06.249 --> 28:08.208
And it isn't good.

28:10.210 --> 28:14.127
This city is about
to be attacked from space.

28:14.170 --> 28:18.392
Our only chance is to buy
protection from the Morks.

28:18.435 --> 28:21.047
You know that big facility
out on Blake Island?

28:23.353 --> 28:26.530
150 outliers need to report
there by sundown.

28:26.574 --> 28:29.664
- As close as we can get.

28:29.708 --> 28:32.493
♪

28:32.536 --> 28:35.757
I know what I'm asking.

28:35.801 --> 28:37.672
If you volunteer,

28:37.716 --> 28:39.674
our intel suggest
you'll be fighting

28:39.718 --> 28:43.199
on the front line
of an unknown war.

28:43.243 --> 28:46.420
I can't even imagine
what you'll be facing.

28:46.463 --> 28:49.162
- We don't have anywhere
close to 150.

28:49.205 --> 28:51.468
- We'll reach out
to the other groups.

28:51.512 --> 28:53.688
But we have to lead
by example.

28:53.732 --> 29:00.739
♪

29:07.223 --> 29:09.225
- I'll go.

29:09.269 --> 29:14.840
♪

29:14.883 --> 29:18.191
I believe in this man.

29:18.234 --> 29:21.847
If he says that's
the situation, it's true.

29:21.890 --> 29:24.240
♪

29:24.284 --> 29:26.329
I know the odds of coming
back are bad.

29:26.373 --> 29:30.594
But we were trained to fight,
so there's always a chance.

29:30.638 --> 29:32.858
And if we go,
we'll be buying time

29:32.901 --> 29:34.860
for everyone else in this city.

29:34.903 --> 29:40.169
♪

29:40.213 --> 29:43.869
You ever want to be a part of
something bigger than yourself?

29:43.912 --> 29:46.393
Well, this is it.

29:46.436 --> 29:49.178
♪

29:49.222 --> 29:50.571
- I'll go.

29:50.614 --> 29:53.095
♪

29:53.139 --> 29:54.618
- Me too.

29:54.662 --> 29:57.404
- And me.
- I'm in.

29:57.447 --> 30:04.498
♪

30:12.811 --> 30:12.985
.

30:16.292 --> 30:17.467
- Too grim.

30:19.861 --> 30:21.471
Leave it.

30:24.431 --> 30:26.476
- They're ready for you.

30:39.925 --> 30:42.405
- All of you worked
for Mr. Kynes,

30:42.449 --> 30:45.756
so I presume you have
some loyalty to him.

30:45.800 --> 30:47.889
If you want to leave
your positions,

30:47.933 --> 30:49.586
I will give you a free pass.

30:49.630 --> 30:51.414
Just walk out the door.

31:00.815 --> 31:03.862
Not the choice I would
have made, but I respect it.

31:05.037 --> 31:07.604
And what do I do
with the rest of you?

31:07.648 --> 31:08.910
I have to get this Colony

31:08.954 --> 31:10.694
back on its feet
as soon as possible,

31:10.738 --> 31:12.783
and, unfortunately,
I cannot ask Switzerland

31:12.827 --> 31:14.394
for new officials.

31:14.437 --> 31:17.397
But how do I know that you
won't be plotting

31:17.440 --> 31:19.529
behind my back?

31:19.573 --> 31:21.749
You, what's your name?

31:21.792 --> 31:23.664
- Roy Morrow.

31:23.707 --> 31:26.319
- The chief technology officer.

31:29.496 --> 31:31.802
- Don't move!
- Sit.

31:31.846 --> 31:33.935
Please.

31:33.979 --> 31:37.634
Mr. Morrow erased
the Seattle database,

31:37.678 --> 31:39.985
which means
that we know nothing

31:40.028 --> 31:41.943
about the people
in this Colony,

31:41.987 --> 31:44.119
which is going to be
very inconvenient

31:44.163 --> 31:46.643
when the insurrection
inevitably arises.

31:47.993 --> 31:51.953
You chose my side when you
didn't walk out of this room.

31:51.997 --> 31:55.826
And we are not going to let

31:55.870 --> 31:57.654
this Colony fall into anarchy.

31:57.698 --> 32:00.831
We will provide law and order,
and we will give our Hosts

32:00.875 --> 32:03.922
every bit of help that we can
in the coming war.

32:03.965 --> 32:07.577
That is how we will survive.

32:08.709 --> 32:10.493
Get ready.

32:10.537 --> 32:12.147
We've got work to do.

32:15.194 --> 32:17.152
♪

32:27.771 --> 32:30.774
- I'm sorry about your friend.

32:30.818 --> 32:33.168
- He did what he needed to do.

32:33.212 --> 32:34.778
- Hey...

32:36.041 --> 32:37.781
I'm still sorry.

32:38.957 --> 32:40.871
- Me too.

32:42.569 --> 32:46.007
- Kynes gave me the location
of the other facility.

32:46.051 --> 32:49.706
It's easy to defend,
loaded with supplies.

32:49.750 --> 32:50.969
Here.

32:52.405 --> 32:55.538
- We're putting a lot
of faith in that man.

32:55.582 --> 32:57.105
- Well, the Occupation
hates him,

32:57.149 --> 32:58.846
so he can't be all bad.

32:58.889 --> 33:01.022
- Been talking to those
other outlier groups.

33:01.066 --> 33:04.547
They seem organized,
professional.

33:04.591 --> 33:06.810
They just need
a reason to rally.

33:06.854 --> 33:10.727
- Then it doesn't matter
if Kynes is the real deal.

33:10.771 --> 33:13.034
Let him give people
a reason to believe,

33:13.078 --> 33:16.733
and then once everyone's headed
in the same direction,

33:16.777 --> 33:18.822
you can dump them
if you have to.

33:18.866 --> 33:20.737
- Look at you...

33:20.781 --> 33:22.913
finding your inner Machiavelli.

33:22.957 --> 33:24.611
- Well, if you're
gonna be a leader,

33:24.654 --> 33:27.135
someone has to whisper
dark ideas in your ear.

33:28.615 --> 33:31.052
- I'll put a call out
to those other groups

33:31.096 --> 33:33.011
to meet us at the bunker.

33:34.099 --> 33:36.014
We'll see who shows up.

33:45.806 --> 33:48.504
- Yeah.

33:56.034 --> 34:00.081
What's going on?
- Just some political stuff.

34:00.125 --> 34:03.084
Someone new's in charge
of the bloc.

34:03.128 --> 34:06.000
- No, I-I mean, what's going on
with Mom and Dad?

34:09.221 --> 34:11.658
- They got involved
in some things.

34:11.701 --> 34:14.574
It's not safe for us
to be around.

34:14.617 --> 34:17.229
- I thought they weren't
gonna do that anymore.

34:17.272 --> 34:19.231
- Well, they did.

34:26.673 --> 34:29.632
Look, I don't know
what's gonna happen.

34:29.676 --> 34:31.112
Maybe we'll see them tomorrow,

34:31.156 --> 34:34.637
or maybe we won't see them
for a while.

34:34.681 --> 34:36.117
But they love you.

34:39.164 --> 34:46.171
♪

34:52.873 --> 34:55.005
Attention, all refugees.

34:55.049 --> 34:59.009
Please exit the area
in a calm and orderly fashion.

34:59.053 --> 35:02.665
I repeat--
please exit the area

35:02.709 --> 35:04.885
in a calm
and orderly fashion.

35:04.928 --> 35:06.626
Thank you.

35:10.586 --> 35:12.632
- Mr. Kynes ordered us
to evacuate the camp.

35:12.675 --> 35:13.981
I told everyone who could walk

35:14.024 --> 35:15.635
to get as far away from here
as possible.

35:15.678 --> 35:17.027
- I thought Kynes wasn't
in charge anymore.

35:17.071 --> 35:18.855
- Mr. Kynes is the reason
I took the job.

35:18.899 --> 35:20.683
He's the one I trust.

35:20.727 --> 35:22.859
- What do you think
is gonna happen?

35:22.903 --> 35:25.166
- Nothing good.
- But you're still here.

35:25.210 --> 35:26.341
- We have a number of refugees

35:26.385 --> 35:28.169
who aren't healthy enough
to move,

35:28.213 --> 35:30.258
and someone's got to look
after them.

35:33.218 --> 35:34.741
What's that?

35:39.049 --> 35:40.747
- I'm trying to find my kids.

35:40.790 --> 35:42.792
And I think this woman
might know where they are.

35:42.836 --> 35:45.055
Attention, all refugees.

35:45.099 --> 35:49.016
Please exit the area
in a calm and orderly fashion.

35:49.059 --> 35:52.715
I repeat--
please exit the area

35:52.759 --> 35:55.065
in a calm and orderly fashion.

35:55.109 --> 35:56.806
Thank you.

35:58.156 --> 36:00.767
- That's the address.

36:00.810 --> 36:02.203
- Thank you.

36:02.247 --> 36:04.684
[indistinct chatter
over radio]

36:04.727 --> 36:07.904
- I don't have enough staff
for the refugees we have left.

36:07.948 --> 36:10.603
I could use your help.

36:10.646 --> 36:12.735
- I have to find my kids.

36:12.779 --> 36:14.998
I will come back if I can.

36:19.220 --> 36:22.092
I wasn't fair to you, was I?

36:22.136 --> 36:23.920
- We all do what we have to do.

36:26.967 --> 36:33.887
♪

36:39.980 --> 36:43.113
- Press forward!
Move it! Take positions!

36:43.157 --> 36:46.073
- Stop right there!
I said stop!

36:46.116 --> 36:49.119
Identify yourselves!
- We're outliers...

36:49.163 --> 36:51.296
here to turn ourselves over.

36:58.390 --> 36:58.825
.

37:16.930 --> 37:20.455
- Started about
20 minutes ago, sir.

37:20.499 --> 37:22.805
- I didn't realize there
were drones in Seattle.

37:22.849 --> 37:24.154
- Kynes didn't want them.

37:24.198 --> 37:26.331
But they were still here
just in case.

37:26.374 --> 37:30.248
- To join the fight.

37:30.291 --> 37:32.206
Close all the gateways.

37:32.250 --> 37:34.730
- Sir, we still have personnel
outside the Wall.

37:36.950 --> 37:39.082
I'll get it done.
- Copy.

37:40.780 --> 37:42.434
- That was the island.

37:42.477 --> 37:46.133
150 outliers have reached
the facility, safe and sound.

37:46.176 --> 37:47.700
- Thank God.

37:47.743 --> 37:50.180
Maybe our Hosts will actually
defend this place.

37:50.224 --> 37:52.313
- Yeah, just not
with drones.

37:52.357 --> 37:54.315
- No, when it comes to any
potential insurrection,

37:54.359 --> 37:56.012
we're on our own.

37:56.056 --> 37:58.014
It's just you and me
and a few thousand Grayhats

37:58.058 --> 38:00.278
to hold this whole city.

38:00.321 --> 38:04.412
- Well, don't forget
our converted Boy Scouts.

38:06.022 --> 38:08.851
- If we don't play
this just right,

38:08.895 --> 38:11.332
we're gonna wind up
with our heads on pikes.

38:15.031 --> 38:17.991
[indistinct chatter,
horns honking]

38:18.034 --> 38:20.036
♪

38:23.388 --> 38:26.086
- What the hell's going on
up there?

38:26.129 --> 38:28.218
- Excuse me.
What's going on?

38:28.262 --> 38:31.352
- Gateway is shut down.

38:31.396 --> 38:34.268
- Are we leaving,
or are we not?

38:37.315 --> 38:42.407
♪

38:42.450 --> 38:43.886
- All clear.

38:46.933 --> 38:49.283
- The place is stocked
like Fort Benning.

38:49.327 --> 38:51.024
We could live in there
for a decade

38:51.067 --> 38:54.244
and run a full-scale insurgency
when we emerge.

38:54.288 --> 38:56.812
Get everyone inside.
- Yes, sir.

38:58.771 --> 39:00.860
- So Kynes wasn't lying.

39:02.035 --> 39:03.950
- There's some crazy stuff
in there--

39:03.993 --> 39:07.170
laboratories, advanced
communications equipment--

39:45.992 --> 39:49.604
- I am.

39:49.648 --> 39:53.608
Are you the cavalry?
- Yeah...

39:53.652 --> 39:55.349
I guess we are.

39:58.483 --> 40:00.136
- Come inside.

40:00.180 --> 40:02.487
Introduce yourselves.

40:02.530 --> 40:05.968
And then we can talk
about how to raise holy hell.

40:06.012 --> 40:08.884
♪

40:08.928 --> 40:12.584
- Thank you, dear Lord,
for new friends under our roof

40:12.627 --> 40:15.500
and keeping us safe
on this dangerous day.

40:15.543 --> 40:17.980
Amen.

40:29.339 --> 40:36.216
♪

41:19.433 --> 41:26.092
♪

41:58.472 --> 42:05.523
♪
